@mkswd Isn't this changing the logic of the code?
Before the change, if `fnInfo.DefiningLanguageMode` was null, then `.HasValue` would terminate the `if` statement and function would `return true` regardless of `this.ExecutionContext.LanguageMode`.
After the change, if `fnInfo.DefiningLanguageMode` is `null` for some reason, then default of `enum PSLanguageMode` (which happens to be `FullLanguage = 0`) will be used for comparison and that may `return false` depending on the value of `this.ExecutionContext.LanguageMode`.
